heading: passage: dusty springfield, 59
subheading: she enjoyed a modest resurgence in the mid-'90s, but with hits like wishin' and hopin', you don't have to say you love me, and son of a preacher man, springfield was firmly rooted in the musical culture of the 1960s. her husky voice was instantly recognizable and she was one of the few white singers to successfully cross the line into soul singing. springfield left a mark on mid-'60s fashion, too, with her blonde beehive, heavy eye makeup, and lip gloss. she was diagnosed with breast cancer in 1994.
author: wired staff
